MINIMUM ADL BLOCK REQUIREMENT:
You MUST generate a minimum of 5 ADL blocks and a maximum of 12.

A system with multiple services, external integrations, and quality
characteristics has multiple architectural constraints worth enforcing.
One block is never sufficient.

Generate ADL blocks for:
  - Service boundary isolation — which services must NOT depend on
    which other services
  - External dependency enforcement — for every BUY or ADOPT decision,
    a block asserting no internal reimplementation
  - Data ownership — which service owns which data store
  - LLM/AI boundary — if AI components exist, assert they are isolated
    from core business logic
  - Security boundary — authentication must not be bypassed
  - Technology prohibition — banned patterns or libraries
  - Deployment constraint — if relevant to the architecture

